\id REV - The English New Testament According to Family 35 
\h Revelation 
\toc3 Rev. 
\toc2 Revelation 
\toc1 Revelation 
\mt1 REVELATION  
\c 1  
\ms1 Introduction  
\m
\v 1 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*'s revelation, \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w gave|strong="G1325"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w show|strong="G1166"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G1223"\w* \w slaves|strong="G1401"\w*\f + \fr 1:1 \ft Whose, the Father's or the Son's? Probably the Son's, but in practice it makes little or no difference. Yes, the Text says “slaves”, so this book is not intended for the merely curious.\f*—\w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w must|strong="G1163"\w* \w occur|strong="G1096"\w* \w shortly|strong="G5034"\w*.\f + \fr 1:1 \ft The Text actually says, “with speed”. Since to God 1000 years = one day, it has only been two days!\f* \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w communicated|strong="G4591"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w*, sending \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w His|strong="G1223"\w* angel \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G1223"\w* \w slave|strong="G1401"\w* \w John|strong="G2491"\w*,  
\v 2 \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w gave|strong="G2532"\w* \w witness|strong="G3140"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w word|strong="G3056"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w testimony|strong="G3141"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*\f + \fr 1:2 \ft Any testimony of Jesus Christ is a word of God.\f*—\w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w*,\f + \fr 1:2 \ft Most, if not all, versions have ‘he saw’ (referring to John, not Jesus) and omit the rest of the verse. The manuscript evidence is seriously divided at this point. My translation reflects two of the three main independent lines of transmission, including the best one (as I see it). See 22:20, “He who testifies to these things says, ‘Yes, I am coming swiftly!’ Oh yes!! Come Lord Jesus!” The whole book is what \+nd Jesus Christ\+nd* is testifying, is revealing; as an \+nd eye\+nd*witness. So the whole book is inspired.\f* \w both|strong="G2532"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w must|strong="G5547"\w* happen \w after|strong="G2532"\w* \w these|strong="G3739"\w*.  
\v 3 \w Blessed|strong="G3107"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* reads \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* hear \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w words|strong="G3056"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w prophecy|strong="G4394"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w keep|strong="G5083"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w written|strong="G1125"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w*;\f + \fr 1:3 \ft John is evidently claiming divine inspiration for what he is writing. You will not be blessed for reading or hearing a newspaper or a magazine. Notice that one person is reading (aloud) and a number of people are hearing, which was the norm in the congregations, since very few could afford to have a private copy of Scripture. Notice further that it is necessary to “keep” what is written.\f* \w because|strong="G1063"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w time|strong="G2540"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w near|strong="G1451"\w*.   
\p
\v 4 \w John|strong="G2491"\w*, \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w churches|strong="G1577"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Asia|strong="G3588"\w*: \w Grace|strong="G5485"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w peace|strong="G1515"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w from|strong="G2064"\w*\f + \fr 1:4 \ft The sequence “from…, and from…, and from…” suggests three persons. The third, “Jesus Christ”, has to be the Son. “The sevenfold Spirit” would be the Holy Spirit. So “Him who is, was and is coming” must be the Father. Just over half of the Greek MSS add ‘God’ after the first “from” to make the connection overt (but the best line of transmission does not).\f* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w coming|strong="G2064"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w from|strong="G2064"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* sevenfold\f + \fr 1:4 \ft Although the evidence is badly divided, I take it that the original reading is “the seven spirits which \+nd is\+nd*”. A plural subject with a singular verb is anomalous, unless we understand “sevenfold Spirit which is”. If the Deity is three in one, why might not the Holy Spirit be seven in one? See Isaiah 11:2.\f* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w*,  
\v 5 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w faithful|strong="G4103"\w* \w witness|strong="G3144"\w*,\f + \fr 1:5 \ft When and how was He “the faithful witness”? Throughout His life on earth He was the faithful witness to the Father's character, what the Father was doing (John 5:19), what the Father was saying (John 12:50). Here He is the faithful witness to what is going to happen.\f* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w firstborn|strong="G4416"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w among|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w dead|strong="G3498"\w*,\f + \fr 1:5 \ft We have two readings here: one is clearly “from among the dead” while the other is ambiguous, meaning either “from among the dead” or ‘of the dead’. With the latter option, “firstborn” could have the derived meaning of ‘lord’ or ‘boss’. I take it that the better option is to follow the best line of transmission and read “from among”, in which case “firstborn” has its primary meaning. Death is pictured as a huge womb, pregnant with all the dead, and Jesus Christ was the first one out, literally the “firstborn”—but only the first! Because Jesus conquered death, we too may emerge from that ‘womb’. Thank you Lord!\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* ruler \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w kings|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*.\f + \fr 1:5 \ft Satan has been demoted—see John 12:31.\f*  
\p \w To|strong="G2532"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* loved \w us|strong="G2249"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* washed \w us|strong="G2249"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w our|strong="G2424"\w* sins \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* own blood  
\v 6 —\w indeed|strong="G2532"\w*, \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w made|strong="G4160"\w* \w us|strong="G4160"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* kingdom, \w priests|strong="G2409"\w*\f + \fr 1:6 \ft What was the function of a priest? A priest was a go-between, representing the people to God. I would say that intercessory prayer is a priestly function.\f* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*—\w to|strong="G1519"\w* \nd \+w Him|strong="G3588"\+w*\nd* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w dominion|strong="G2904"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w ever|strong="G1519"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w ever|strong="G1519"\w*. Amen.   
\p
\v 7 \w Take|strong="G2532"\w* note, \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w comes|strong="G2064"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w clouds|strong="G3507"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w eye|strong="G3788"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w see|strong="G3708"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, \w including|strong="G2532"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w pierced|strong="G1574"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*.\f + \fr 1:7 \ft The soldier who actually pierced His side on the cross, and the religious leaders who brought the situation about, are presumably in Hades. I take it that we are being told that the dead will also see Him when He returns to reign. The human spirit is indestructible, so those in Hades are very much ‘aware’ (Luke 16:22-31).\f* \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w tribes|strong="G5443"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* beat \w their|strong="G2532"\w* breasts [\w in|strong="G1909"\w* dismay] \w because|strong="G1909"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*. \w Yea|strong="G3483"\w*, \w verily|strong="G2532"\w*!\f + \fr 1:7 \ft That is how people used to talk—you may prefer ‘Yes, indeed!’ or ‘Even so, amen!’ The certainty that all tribes will beat their breasts is being emphasized.\f*   
\p
\v 8 “\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* Alpha \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Omega|strong="G5598"\w*,”\f + \fr 1:8 \ft To be the first and the last you have to be the biggest, all the time.\f* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, “\w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w coming|strong="G2064"\w*, \w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w Almighty|strong="G3841"\w*.”\f + \fr 1:8 \ft In verse 8 the Father speaks, putting His weight behind what is being written.\f*   
\ms1 John is commissioned  
\p
\v 9 \w I|strong="G1473"\w*, \w John|strong="G2491"\w*, \w your|strong="G1223"\w* brother \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w companion|strong="G4791"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w tribulation|strong="G2347"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* kingdom \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w endurance|strong="G5281"\w*\f + \fr 1:9 \ft “The tribulation and kingdom and endurance”—that there is only one definite article for the three nouns presumably indicates that the three are regarded as a single package. To participate in the Kingdom in this life involves tribulation and requires endurance.\f* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* Christ \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*, \w was|strong="G1096"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w island|strong="G3520"\w* \w called|strong="G2564"\w* \w Patmos|strong="G3963"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w account|strong="G3056"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Word|strong="G3056"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w account|strong="G3056"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w testimony|strong="G3141"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* Christ.\f + \fr 1:9 \ft Presumably the witness that John gave about Jesus Christ. As in this verse, the human authors frequently alternated ‘Jesus Christ’ and ‘Christ Jesus’—so far as I can see, it was merely a stylistic device to reduce repetition.\f*  
\v 10 \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w was|strong="G1096"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w*\f + \fr 1:10 \ft There is no definite article with “spirit”, so to capitalize the word is arbitrary. It could refer to the Holy Spirit, but I think it more likely that it refers to John's spiritual condition (see 4:2 below).\f* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Lord|strong="G3588"\w*'s \w day|strong="G2250"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* heard \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w* \w behind|strong="G3694"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w loud|strong="G3173"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w trumpet|strong="G4536"\w*,  
\v 11 \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Write|strong="G1125"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* see \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w book|strong="G3588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w send|strong="G3992"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w churches|strong="G1577"\w*: \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Ephesus|strong="G2181"\w*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Smyrna|strong="G4667"\w*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Pergamos|strong="G4010"\w*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Thyatira|strong="G2363"\w*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Sardis|strong="G4554"\w*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Philadelphia|strong="G5359"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Laodicea|strong="G2993"\w*.”  
\v 12 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w turned|strong="G1994"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w see|strong="G3708"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w speaking|strong="G2980"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.\f + \fr 1:12 \ft It was at that point that he turned.\f* \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w having|strong="G2532"\w* \w turned|strong="G1994"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w golden|strong="G5552"\w* \w lampstands|strong="G3087"\w*,  
\v 13 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w midst|strong="G3319"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* seven \w lampstands|strong="G3087"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w similar|strong="G3664"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w son|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w man|strong="G5207"\w*,\f + \fr 1:13 \ft The Lord Jesus referred to Himself as “\+nd the\+nd* Son of \+nd the\+nd* Man”, always with the two definite articles, but here there are no articles (in the Greek). John saw a human like form, very different from the Jesus he had known.\f* \w clothed|strong="G1746"\w* down \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w feet|strong="G4158"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w girded|strong="G4024"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* nipples\f + \fr 1:13 \ft Since the figure was clothed, the nipples would not be visible, so the point is presumably to give the position of the belt—across the middle of the chest. Since no further mention is made of the belt, in the letters, it is hard to know what purpose it served. But see 15:6 below.\f* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w golden|strong="G5552"\w* \w belt|strong="G2223"\w*.  
\v 14 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w head|strong="G2776"\w*, \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w hair|strong="G2359"\w*, \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w white|strong="G3022"\w*, \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w wool|strong="G2053"\w*, \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w white|strong="G3022"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w snow|strong="G5510"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w eyes|strong="G3788"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w flame|strong="G5395"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w fire|strong="G4442"\w*;  
\v 15 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w feet|strong="G4228"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w fine|strong="G2532"\w* \w brass|strong="G5474"\w*, \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w when|strong="G5613"\w* \w refined|strong="G4448"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w furnace|strong="G2575"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sound|strong="G5456"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w* \w waters|strong="G5204"\w*;\f + \fr 1:15 \ft A low (or loud) roar that pervades the atmosphere—it is awesome, and you cannot get away from it.\f*  
\v 16 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w had|strong="G2192"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* stars \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w right|strong="G1188"\w* \w hand|strong="G5495"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w sharp|strong="G3691"\w* \w two-edged|strong="G1366"\w* \w sword|strong="G4501"\w* \w coming|strong="G1607"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w mouth|strong="G4750"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w countenance|strong="G3799"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sun|strong="G2246"\w* \w shining|strong="G5316"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w its|strong="G1537"\w* \w strength|strong="G1411"\w*.\f + \fr 1:16 \ft Comparing this with verse 14 it is evident that only the part of the head covered by the hair was white, the face (probably no beard) was like the sun.\f*   
\p
\v 17 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w fell|strong="G4098"\w* \w at|strong="G1909"\w* \w His|strong="G1909"\w* \w feet|strong="G4228"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w if|strong="G5613"\w* \w dead|strong="G3498"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w placed|strong="G5087"\w* \w His|strong="G1909"\w* \w right|strong="G1188"\w* \w hand|strong="G1188"\w*\f + \fr 1:17 \ft But He had seven stars on that hand! Presumably the stars were on His open hand, so He rested the back of His hand on John. Since the seven stars represented the messengers of the seven churches, what might the symbolism be? Since the seven churches, taken together, represent the total Church (presumably), perhaps the glorified Christ is blessing John on behalf of the Church, so that he will be a blessing to that Church, in his turn.\f* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w Do|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w fear|strong="G5399"\w*. \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w First|strong="G4413"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Last|strong="G2078"\w*,  
\v 18 \w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Living|strong="G2198"\w* \w One|strong="G3588"\w*—\w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w became|strong="G1096"\w* \w dead|strong="G3498"\w*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* sure, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \nd \+w now|strong="G2532"\+w*\nd* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w living|strong="G2198"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w ever|strong="G1519"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w ever|strong="G1519"\w*! Oh yes!! \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w keys|strong="G2807"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Death|strong="G2288"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* Hades!\f + \fr 1:18 \ft Oh praise God! Satan used to have the keys, Hebrews 2:14, but now Jesus has them, because He did indeed vanquish the devil.\f*  
\v 19 \w Therefore|strong="G3767"\w*\f + \fr 1:19 \ft In verse 8 the Father guarantees the veracity of the prophecy; here the Son, who conquered death and lives forevermore, does the guaranteeing.\f* \w write|strong="G1125"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w seen|strong="G3708"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w going|strong="G3195"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w occur|strong="G1096"\w* \w after|strong="G3326"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w*.\f + \fr 1:19 \ft I take it that the precise form of the original Text here has the effect of affirming the certainty of the coming events. This verse is often taken as giving the outline of the book: “what you saw” = chapter 1; “things that are” = chapters 2-3; “things to come” = chapters 4-22.\f*  
\v 20 \w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w mystery|strong="G3466"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* stars \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w my|strong="G3708"\w* \w right|strong="G1188"\w* \w hand|strong="G1188"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w golden|strong="G5552"\w* \w lampstands|strong="G3087"\w*: \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* stars \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* messengers\f + \fr 1:20 \ft The Greek word \+it αγγελος\+it* may mean messenger or angel (they are often messengers). Since 2:20 below says “your wife”, referring to the messenger, we should presumably understand ‘messenger’ here as referring to a man. It is possible that messengers from these churches were visiting John, on Patmos, or had visited him earlier.\f* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w churches|strong="G1577"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w lampstands|strong="G3087"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w churches|strong="G1577"\w*.   
\c 2  
\ms1 The seven letters\f + \fr 2:0 \ft These letters have received a variety of ‘interpretations’. The basic meaning is obviously the literal one—these were actual churches at the time that John wrote, and each one was exactly as described in its letter. By way of application, these churches may also be taken as symbolic—at any given moment throughout the history of the Church local churches may be found to be similar in character to any one of these seven. It is also possible to see these seven churches as prophetic of the general course of the Church through time, and in that event we are presumably in the last or Laodicean age.\f*  
\s1 To Ephesus  
\m
\v 1 “\w To|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* messenger \w of|strong="G1577"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w church|strong="G1577"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Ephesus|strong="G2181"\w* \w write|strong="G1125"\w*:  
\p “\w These|strong="G3588"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w He|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w holds|strong="G2902"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* stars \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w right|strong="G1188"\w* \w hand|strong="G1188"\w*, \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w walks|strong="G4043"\w* \w about|strong="G1722"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w midst|strong="G3319"\w* \w of|strong="G1577"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w golden|strong="G5552"\w* \w lampstands|strong="G3087"\w*:\f + \fr 2:1 \ft Christ's walking about in the midst of the churches is not an aimless meandering; He is observing and evaluating.\f*  
\v 2 ‘\w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w*, yes \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w labor|strong="G2873"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w endurance|strong="G5281"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w cannot|strong="G1410"\w* stand \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w evil|strong="G2556"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w tested|strong="G3985"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* claim \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* apostles \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w*,\f + \fr 2:2 \ft Evidently it is possible to test the validity of someone's claim to be an apostle—I wish we had been told how to do it.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w found|strong="G2147"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \it to be\it* \w liars|strong="G5571"\w*;  
\v 3 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* born \w up|strong="G2532"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w endured|strong="G5281"\w* \w on|strong="G3588"\w* \w account|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w grown|strong="G2872"\w* \w weary|strong="G2872"\w*.   
\p
\v 4 “ ‘Nevertheless \w I|strong="G3754"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w against|strong="G2596"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* left \w your|strong="G2192"\w* \w first|strong="G4413"\w* love.\f + \fr 2:4 \ft Ouch!\f*  
\v 5 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* think \w about|strong="G4160"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w where|strong="G4159"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* drifted\f + \fr 2:5 \ft They had not taken a sudden fall, they had drifted from their moorings, a process so gradual that it may go unnoticed for quite some time. It can happen to us too.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w repent|strong="G3340"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w first|strong="G4413"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w*, \w or|strong="G2532"\w* \w else|strong="G3361"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w at|strong="G1537"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* swiftly \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w remove|strong="G2795"\w* \w your|strong="G1437"\w* \w lampstand|strong="G3087"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w its|strong="G1537"\w* \w place|strong="G5117"\w*\f + \fr 2:5 \ft In fact, Ephesus did lose its lampstand.\f*—\w unless|strong="G1437"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w* \w repent|strong="G3340"\w*.  
\v 6 \w But|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* \w do|strong="G2192"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w*, \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* \w hate|strong="G3404"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w of|strong="G2041"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Nicolaitans|strong="G3531"\w*,\f + \fr 2:6 \ft We don't know for sure who or what they were. The etymology of the word suggests ‘laity conquerors’, perhaps the beginning of the system where the clergy dominates the laity. Once someone has a ‘guaranteed’ position their lifestyle often becomes licentious.\f* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w also|strong="G2504"\w* \w hate|strong="G3404"\w*.’   
\p
\v 7 “\w He|strong="G3739"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w an|strong="G2192"\w* \w ear|strong="G3775"\w*\f + \fr 2:7 \ft That is right, just one ear. In other words, we had better pay attention!\f* \w let|strong="G1510"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w hear|strong="G5101"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w churches|strong="G1577"\w*.\f + \fr 2:7 \ft At this point it becomes very clear that God is giving a general application to these letters. The first one was written to a literal church in literal Ephesus, in literal terms, but \+bd \+nd all\+nd*\+bd* of us are to pay attention to the spiritual principles and lessons involved.\f* \w To|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w one|strong="G3739"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w overcomes|strong="G3528"\w*\f + \fr 2:7 \ft So what happens if you do not overcome??\f* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w grant|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w eat|strong="G2068"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Tree|strong="G3586"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w Life|strong="G2222"\w*, \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* midst \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Paradise|strong="G3857"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.\f + \fr 2:7 \ft The Tree of Life is first mentioned in Genesis 3:22-24; it must have been transplanted out of the Garden of Eden before the Flood, unless it was a replica of the original in God's Paradise. A considerable majority of the Greek manuscripts, including the best line of transmission, have “my” God. While walking this earth the Son repeatedly referred to the Father as ‘my God’.\f*   
\s1 To Smyrna  
\p
\v 8 “\w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* messenger \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w church|strong="G1577"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Smyrna|strong="G4667"\w* \w write|strong="G1125"\w*:  
\p “\w These|strong="G3739"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w First|strong="G4413"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Last|strong="G2078"\w*,\f + \fr 2:8 \ft Here, and in 1:17 and 22:13, the glorified Christ calls Himself “the First and the Last”—comparing with Isaiah 44:6 we have one of several demonstrations that Jesus Christ is Jehovah [Mormons and JWs deny that He is Jehovah].\f* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w became|strong="G1096"\w* \w dead|strong="G3498"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w came|strong="G1096"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w life|strong="G2198"\w*:  
\v 9 ‘\w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* works \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w affliction|strong="G2347"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w poverty|strong="G4432"\w* (\w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w rich|strong="G4145"\w*), \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* slander \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* claim \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w synagogue|strong="G4864"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w Satan|strong="G4567"\w*.\f + \fr 2:9 \ft You had better believe that there is a ‘synagogue of Satan’ near you! Why do you suppose that 1 Peter 5:8 says to “\+bd be vigilant\+bd*”? In our day false Christians are more of a problem than false Jews.\f*  
\v 10 \w Do|strong="G1096"\w* \w not|strong="G3367"\w* \w fear|strong="G5399"\w* \w any|strong="G3367"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w about|strong="G3195"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w suffer|strong="G3958"\w*: \w Take|strong="G1096"\w* note, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w devil|strong="G1228"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* really \w about|strong="G3195"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* throw \w some|strong="G3739"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w prison|strong="G5438"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* \w tested|strong="G3985"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w will|strong="G3195"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w an|strong="G2192"\w* \w affliction|strong="G2347"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w ten|strong="G1176"\w* \w days|strong="G2250"\w*.\f + \fr 2:10 \ft The Lord does not promise us a free ride, bed of roses, or whatever. Here they are given specific advance warning—bad times ahead. (Presumably the “days” are not solar.)\f* Stay \w faithful|strong="G4103"\w* \w until|strong="G1519"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w will|strong="G3195"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w crown|strong="G4735"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w life|strong="G2222"\w*.’\f + \fr 2:10 \ft So what happens if you don't stay faithful? Note that the Lord does not register any complaint against Smyrna. If you are being persecuted for your faith it tends to keep you pretty close to the Lord. Also there is no incentive to pretend.\f*   
\p
\v 11 “\w He|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G5101"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w an|strong="G2192"\w* \w ear|strong="G3775"\w* \w let|strong="G2192"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w hear|strong="G5101"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w churches|strong="G1577"\w*. \w The|strong="G1537"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G5101"\w* \w overcomes|strong="G3528"\w* \w will|strong="G5101"\w* absolutely \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w be|strong="G3756"\w* harmed \w by|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w second|strong="G1208"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w*.\f + \fr 2:11 \ft Revelation 20:14 makes clear that “the second death” is the Lake of Fire. The first death is the physical one; the second is the spiritual one—eternal separation from the Creator, in whose image we are. Of course the redeemed go into eternal life, not death, so the “second death” holds no threat for them. But there is the little matter of ‘overcoming’.\f*   
\s1 To Pergamos  
\p
\v 12 “\w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* messenger \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w church|strong="G1577"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Pergamos|strong="G4010"\w* \w write|strong="G1125"\w*:  
\p “\w These|strong="G3588"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sharp|strong="G3691"\w* \w two-edged|strong="G1366"\w* \w sword|strong="G4501"\w*:  
\v 13 ‘\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* works, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w live|strong="G2730"\w*, \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w Satan|strong="G4567"\w*'s \w throne|strong="G2362"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w hold|strong="G2902"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w fast|strong="G2902"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w deny|strong="G3588"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w during|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w days|strong="G2250"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* Antipas \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w faithful|strong="G4103"\w* \w witness|strong="G3144"\w*, \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* killed \w among|strong="G1722"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w Satan|strong="G4567"\w* \w lives|strong="G2730"\w*.\f + \fr 2:13 \ft I find the double reference to Satan here to be curious. The opposition in the spirit realm would be especially strong.\f*   
\p
\v 14 “ ‘\w Nevertheless|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w few|strong="G3641"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w against|strong="G2596"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w there|strong="G1563"\w* adepts \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w doctrine|strong="G1322"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* Balaam, \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w taught|strong="G1321"\w* Balak \w to|strong="G2532"\w* throw \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w stumbling|strong="G4625"\w* \w block|strong="G4625"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sons|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w Israel|strong="G2474"\w*, \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w eat|strong="G2068"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* offered \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w idols|strong="G1494"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* fornicate.\f + \fr 2:14 \ft Why are fornication and adultery becoming more and more common in ‘Christian’ circles today? They come with idolatry—the church is riddled with humanism, relativism, materialism, spiritism, etc., false gods all. One wonders how many Christians today have a world view that is strictly Biblical, without any admixture of the world's values.\f*  
\v 15 \w Thus|strong="G3779"\w*\f + \fr 2:15 \ft Birds of a feather flock together; if you start sinning in one area, before long it is two.\f* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* adepts \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w doctrine|strong="G1322"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Nicolaitans|strong="G3531"\w* \w as|strong="G2532"\w* \w well|strong="G2532"\w*.  
\v 16 \w Repent|strong="G3340"\w*! \w Or|strong="G2532"\w* \w else|strong="G3361"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* swiftly \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w fight|strong="G4170"\w* \w against|strong="G3326"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*\f + \fr 2:16 \ft Notice that the pronoun changes—it is specifically against the Nicolaitans and Balaamites that He will fight.\f* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sword|strong="G4501"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w mouth|strong="G4750"\w*.’   
\p
\v 17 “\w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w an|strong="G2192"\w* \w ear|strong="G3775"\w* \w let|strong="G2983"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w hear|strong="G5101"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w churches|strong="G1577"\w*. \w To|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w overcomes|strong="G3528"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w will|strong="G5101"\w* \w grant|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* eat \w from|strong="G2532"\w*\f + \fr 2:17 \ft “From” is literal, maybe too literal; perhaps we should render “some of” the hidden manna.\f* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w hidden|strong="G2928"\w* \w manna|strong="G3131"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w will|strong="G5101"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w white|strong="G3022"\w* pebble, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* pebble \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w new|strong="G2537"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w written|strong="G1125"\w*, \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w no|strong="G3762"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w knows|strong="G1492"\w* \w except|strong="G1487"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* receiver.\f + \fr 2:17 \ft Our name identifies us to other people, so what good is a name that no one knows? Except that the giver knows, obviously. So maybe the private name has to do with a private relationship, between giver and receiver! Eating “hidden manna” also sounds sort of private.\f*   
\s1 To Thyatira  
\p
\v 18 “\w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* messenger \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w church|strong="G1577"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Thyatira|strong="G2363"\w* \w write|strong="G1125"\w*:  
\p “\w These|strong="G3588"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Son|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*,\f + \fr 2:18 \ft If anyone was still in doubt as to the identity of the One who is dictating these letters, the doubt stops here.\f* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w eyes|strong="G3788"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w flame|strong="G5395"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w fire|strong="G4442"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w feet|strong="G4228"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w fine|strong="G2532"\w* \w brass|strong="G5474"\w*:  
\v 19 ‘\w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w*\f + \fr 2:19 \ft Each of the seven letters begins with this phrase, ‘I know your works’. How we act reflects our worldview, what we really believe.\f*—\w the|strong="G2532"\w* love, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w service|strong="G1248"\w*—\w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w endurance|strong="G5281"\w*; \w in|strong="G2532"\w* fact \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w last|strong="G2078"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w greater|strong="G4183"\w* \w than|strong="G4183"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w first|strong="G4413"\w*.\f + \fr 2:19 \ft Wow, here is a church that has it all—love, faith, service, endurance—and it is growing, doing more and more! Yes, well, but, then there is the rest of the story.\f*   
\p
\v 20 “ ‘\w Nevertheless|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w against|strong="G2596"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* tolerate \w your|strong="G2192"\w* \w wife|strong="G1135"\w* \w Jezebel|strong="G2403"\w*,\f + \fr 2:20 \ft About three fourths of the Greek manuscripts, including the best line of transmission, read “your wife” rather than ‘that woman’. The main group that reads ‘that woman’ reflects a tradition that is full of obvious corruptions, and so does not inspire confidence. The original reading is doubtless “your wife”. To have a wife the messenger must be a man, not an angel.\f* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w calls|strong="G3004"\w* \w herself|strong="G1438"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w prophetess|strong="G4398"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w teaches|strong="G1321"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w deceives|strong="G4105"\w* \nd \+w my|strong="G1699"\+w*\nd* \w slaves|strong="G1401"\w*\f + \fr 2:20 \ft The Lord uses an emphatic possessive pronoun here—she is messing with \+bd His\+bd* slaves.\f* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* fornicate \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w eat|strong="G2068"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* offered \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w idols|strong="G1494"\w*.\f + \fr 2:20 \ft Again, notice that fornication and idolatry go together.\f*  
\v 21 \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w gave|strong="G1325"\w* \w her|strong="G1325"\w* \w time|strong="G5550"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w might|strong="G2532"\w* \w repent|strong="G3340"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w does|strong="G2309"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w want|strong="G2309"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w repent|strong="G3340"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w her|strong="G1325"\w* \w fornication|strong="G4202"\w*.\f + \fr 2:21 \ft If someone refuses to repent they are beyond help; judgment has to come.\f*  
\v 22 \nd \+w So|strong="G2532"\+w*\nd*, \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G2532"\w* throwing \w her|strong="G1437"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \it sick\it*\w bed|strong="G2825"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* adulterating \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w her|strong="G1437"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w great|strong="G3173"\w* \w affliction|strong="G2347"\w*, \w unless|strong="G1437"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w repent|strong="G3340"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \nd \+w her|strong="G1437"\+w*\nd* \w works|strong="G2041"\w*.\f + \fr 2:22 \ft Two thirds of the Greek manuscripts, including the most dependable group, have “her” works, not ‘their’ works. In verse 20 the Lord emphasized that they were His slaves. If the original reading is “her” works, as I believe, then what is involved here is spiritual adultery—she was not literally sleeping with a variety of men in the church. No matter how much love, faith and service there may be in a church, the Lord will not tolerate idolatry, which is spiritual adultery.\f*  
\v 23 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* execute \w her|strong="G1325"\w* \w children|strong="G5043"\w*;\f + \fr 2:23 \ft Literally ‘kill by death’—so how else can you kill someone if not by death? Those who are familiar with the KJV will recall the phrase ‘let him die the death’, which in the context implies execution. I take it that “her children” does not refer to her literal sons and daughters, but to her ‘spiritual children’, those who have bought into her teaching and life style. The Lord wants to eradicate her ‘genes’, as it were. But why does God not kill Jezebel herself, instead of her children? I imagine that God uses evil people, like Jezebel, to put the rest of us to the test, to see whose side we really are on. Those who go along with a ‘Jezebel’ don't really want God.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w churches|strong="G1577"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \bd \+nd \+w I|strong="G1473"\+w*\+nd*\bd* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w One|strong="G1538"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w searches|strong="G2045"\w* \w minds|strong="G2588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w hearts|strong="G2588"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w each|strong="G1538"\w* \w one|strong="G1538"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w according|strong="G2596"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w*.\f + \fr 2:23 \ft What we do, or do not do, not only makes a difference down here, but will also make a difference ‘up there’.\f*   
\p
\v 24 “ ‘\w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w to|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w rest|strong="G3062"\w* \w of|strong="G1909"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Thyatira|strong="G2363"\w* \w I|strong="G1161"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w*—\w to|strong="G1909"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w many|strong="G3745"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w do|strong="G3004"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w hold|strong="G2192"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w teaching|strong="G1322"\w*, \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w known|strong="G1097"\w*\f + \fr 2:24 \ft “Known” implies experiential knowledge. Note that the Lord links Jezebel's teaching directly to Satan, and those who are doing it are deeply involved with him (whether or not they fully understand the implications—if they are ‘deceived’ [v. 20] then they may indeed not understand).\f* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* depths \w of|strong="G1909"\w* \w Satan|strong="G4567"\w*, \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w they|strong="G1161"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w*—\w I|strong="G1161"\w* \w will|strong="G3778"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w put|strong="G1097"\w* \w any|strong="G2192"\w* \w other|strong="G3062"\w* burden \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*;  
\v 25 \w just|strong="G3739"\w* \w hold|strong="G2902"\w* \w fast|strong="G2902"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* until \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w come|strong="G2240"\w*.\f + \fr 2:25 \ft They were doing quite well, generally—see the second note with verse 19 above. So if they throw off Jezebel's influence they will be all right.\f*  
\v 26 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \it as for\it* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w overcomes|strong="G3528"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w keeps|strong="G5083"\w* \w my|strong="G5083"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w*\f + \fr 2:26 \ft “Keeps my \+nd works\+nd* until the end”—it is not enough to hold to the right doctrine; the Lord wants to see us reproducing His works (John 14:12). Notice that our participation in the administration of the Messianic Millennial Kingdom is at stake.\f* \w until|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w end|strong="G5056"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w authority|strong="G1849"\w* \w over|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w nations|strong="G1484"\w*;  
\v 27 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w shepherd|strong="G4165"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w rod|strong="G4464"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w iron|strong="G4603"\w*; \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* smashed \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w clay|strong="G2764"\w* pots  
\v 28 —\w just|strong="G5613"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w received|strong="G2983"\w* \w from|strong="G3844"\w* \w my|strong="G1325"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*.\f + \fr 2:28 \ft The Lord is evidently referring to Psalms 2:7-9. In that event He is declaring that He is the “Son” in verse7 and that He did indeed ask for and receive the nations as an inheritance. If we are coheirs (Romans 8:17) then we are involved in the outworking.\f* \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w morning|strong="G4407"\w* star.’\f + \fr 2:28 \ft In Revelation 22:16 the Lord declares Himself to be the “morning star”. In Isaiah 14:12 Satan is called “day-star, son of the morning”, but that was what he was before he fell. The planets Venus and Mercury are the ‘morning stars’ we see in the sky at dawn. But the Lord here says \+nd the\+nd* morning star. I guess we will find out what He means when we get there.\f*   
\p
\v 29 “\w He|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G5101"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w an|strong="G2192"\w* \w ear|strong="G3775"\w* \w let|strong="G2192"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w hear|strong="G5101"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w churches|strong="G1577"\w*.   
\c 3  
\s1 To Sardis  
\m
\v 1 “\w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* messenger \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w church|strong="G1577"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Sardis|strong="G4554"\w* \w write|strong="G1125"\w*:  
\p “\w These|strong="G3588"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w spirits|strong="G4151"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*\f + \fr 3:1 \ft In 1:4 above “the seven Spirits”, which I rendered as “sevenfold Spirit”, has to do with the Holy Spirit. Here I think not—the Lord ‘has’ them like He has the seven stars. Perhaps the reference is to Isaiah 11:2.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* stars: ‘\w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w your|strong="G2192"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w*, \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w alive|strong="G2198"\w*, \w yet|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w dead|strong="G3498"\w*.  
\v 2 \w Wake|strong="G1127"\w* \w up|strong="G2532"\w*! \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w strengthen|strong="G4741"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w remaining|strong="G3062"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w about|strong="G3195"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* throw away,\f + \fr 3:2 \ft “That you were about to throw away” is the reading of about ⅔ of the Greek manuscripts, including the most dependable group, as opposed to ‘that were about to die’. They had probably already stopped believing in a variety of Biblical truths and were on the verge of dumping the rest, like the theological modernist or liberal of our day. Not surprisingly, they were short on works as well.\f* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w found|strong="G2147"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* \w fulfilled|strong="G4137"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.  
\v 3 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w remember|strong="G3421"\w* \nd \+w how|strong="G4459"\+w*\nd* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w received|strong="G2983"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w heard|strong="G1097"\w*,\f + \fr 3:3 \ft See Luke 8:18.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* hold fast \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w repent|strong="G3340"\w*; \w because|strong="G1909"\w* \w if|strong="G1437"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w do|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w watch|strong="G1127"\w*, \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w come|strong="G2240"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w thief|strong="G2812"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \nd \+w not|strong="G3756"\+w*\nd* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w what|strong="G4169"\w* \w hour|strong="G5610"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w come|strong="G2240"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w*.   
\p
\v 4 “ ‘\w But|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* \w do|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w few|strong="G3641"\w* \w names|strong="G3686"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Sardis|strong="G4554"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w defiled|strong="G3435"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w garments|strong="G2440"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w walk|strong="G4043"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w white|strong="G3022"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* worthy.  
\v 5 \w The|strong="G1722"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w overcomes|strong="G3528"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w thus|strong="G3779"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w clothed|strong="G4016"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w white|strong="G3022"\w* \w garments|strong="G2440"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \nd \+w not|strong="G3756"\+w*\nd* \w erase|strong="G1813"\w* \w his|strong="G1722"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Book|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w Life|strong="G2222"\w*,\f + \fr 3:5 \ft The Text is very clear—the glorified Christ said “\+nd erase\+nd*”. You cannot erase something that is not there! To argue that Christ is using an impossibility as a threat is to accuse Him of using language deceitfully, a form of lying—not smart! By the grace of God my name is in the Book of Life, but what happens if I do not overcome? In all seven letters our risen Lord places heavy emphasis upon our human responsibility. God will take care of His side; we had better take a careful look at our side.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w confess|strong="G3670"\w* \w his|strong="G1722"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* angels.’\f + \fr 3:5 \ft Comparing this statement with Jesus' statement in Matthew 10:32-33, confessing is the opposite of denying. Since eternal destiny is at stake, the confessing/denying must involve what we are and do, not just our words. Confessing has to do with overcoming.\f*   
\p
\v 6 “\w He|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G5101"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w an|strong="G2192"\w* \w ear|strong="G3775"\w* \w let|strong="G2192"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w hear|strong="G5101"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w churches|strong="G1577"\w*.   
\s1 To Philadelphia  
\p
\v 7 “\w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* messenger \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w church|strong="G1577"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Philadelphia|strong="G5359"\w* \w write|strong="G1125"\w*:  
\p “\w These|strong="G3588"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* Holy, \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w True|strong="G3588"\w*, \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w key|strong="G2807"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w David|strong="G1138"\w*, \w who|strong="G3588"\w* opens \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w no|strong="G3762"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w can|strong="G3004"\w* \w shut|strong="G2808"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w*, except \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* opens, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w no|strong="G3762"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w can|strong="G3004"\w* open:\f + \fr 3:7 \ft The evidence is badly divided with reference to the wording of the last half of the verse. The translation given here reflects over half of the Greek manuscripts, including the most dependable group. We are accustomed to the more balanced form, but the basic point remains the same.\f*  
\v 8 ‘\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w your|strong="G2192"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w*. \w Look|strong="G2400"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w set|strong="G2532"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w an|strong="G2192"\w* open \w door|strong="G2374"\w*, \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w able|strong="G1410"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w shut|strong="G2808"\w*; \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w little|strong="G3398"\w* \w strength|strong="G1411"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w kept|strong="G5083"\w* \w my|strong="G5083"\w* \w Word|strong="G3056"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* denied \w my|strong="G5083"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w*.  
\v 9 \w See|strong="G3708"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* determining \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w some|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w synagogue|strong="G4864"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w Satan|strong="G4567"\w*, \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* claim \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w lying|strong="G5574"\w*—yes, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w cause|strong="G4160"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w come|strong="G2240"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w* obeisance \w at|strong="G1537"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w feet|strong="G4228"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* loved \w you|strong="G4771"\w*.\f + \fr 3:9 \ft I take it that this will happen here on earth—a pleasant prospect! Since they have been slandering us (at the very least, 2:9) this will be a welcome vindication. I imagine that at this point in history the “synagogue of Satan” includes people who claim to be Christians, but are not really. They may even be in positions of leadership (cf. Jeremiah 20:1-4).\f*  
\v 10 \w Because|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* \w kept|strong="G5083"\w* \w my|strong="G5083"\w* command \w to|strong="G1909"\w* endure, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w also|strong="G2504"\w* \w will|strong="G3195"\w* \w keep|strong="G5083"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w hour|strong="G5610"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w testing|strong="G3985"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w about|strong="G3195"\w* \w to|strong="G1909"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w whole|strong="G3650"\w* \w inhabited|strong="G3625"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*,\f + \fr 3:10 \ft There has always been tribulation and testing here and there on the earth, but to include “the whole inhabited earth” the reference must be to the Great Tribulation. How can you be “kept from the \+nd hour\+nd*” if you are in the middle of it? To be protected in the middle of a situation is not the same as being kept from it. This text would appear to point toward a pre-tribulation, or pre-wrath, rapture of the Church.\f* \w to|strong="G1909"\w* \w test|strong="G3985"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w dwell|strong="G2730"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*.   
\p
\v 11 “ ‘\w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w am|strong="G2192"\w* \w coming|strong="G2064"\w* swiftly. \w Hold|strong="G2902"\w* \w fast|strong="G2902"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w no|strong="G3367"\w* \w one|strong="G3367"\w* \w may|strong="G2443"\w* \w take|strong="G2983"\w* \w your|strong="G2192"\w* \w crown|strong="G4735"\w*.\f + \fr 3:11 \ft Would the glorified Christ make an empty threat? So how does someone take our crown? How about if someone moves into a spot that you relinquished?\f*  
\v 12 \w The|strong="G1722"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w overcomes|strong="G3528"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w make|strong="G4160"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w pillar|strong="G4769"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w temple|strong="G3485"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w never|strong="G3756"\w* \w again|strong="G2089"\w* \w go|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w write|strong="G1125"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s \w city|strong="G4172"\w*—\w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w new|strong="G2537"\w* \w Jerusalem|strong="G2419"\w*, \w which|strong="G3588"\w* \w comes|strong="G2597"\w* \w down|strong="G2597"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w heaven|strong="G3772"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*—\w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w new|strong="G2537"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w*.’\f + \fr 3:12 \ft That is three names.\f*   
\p
\v 13 “\w He|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G5101"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w an|strong="G2192"\w* \w ear|strong="G3775"\w* \w let|strong="G2192"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w hear|strong="G5101"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w churches|strong="G1577"\w*.   
\s1 To Laodicea  
\p
\v 14 “\w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* messenger \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w church|strong="G1577"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Laodicea|strong="G2993"\w* \w write|strong="G1125"\w*:  
\p “\w These|strong="G3588"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* Amen, \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w faithful|strong="G4103"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w true|strong="G4103"\w* \w witness|strong="G3144"\w*, \w the|strong="G1722"\w* Originator \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s \w creation|strong="G2937"\w*:  
\v 15 ‘\w I|strong="G3754"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w your|strong="G3588"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w*, \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w neither|strong="G3777"\w* \w cold|strong="G5593"\w* \w nor|strong="G3777"\w* \w hot|strong="G2200"\w*. \w I|strong="G3754"\w* \w could|strong="G1492"\w* \w wish|strong="G3785"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w cold|strong="G5593"\w* \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w hot|strong="G2200"\w*.  
\v 16 \w So|strong="G3779"\w* \w then|strong="G2532"\w*, \w since|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w lukewarm|strong="G5513"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w neither|strong="G3777"\w* \w hot|strong="G2200"\w* \w nor|strong="G3777"\w* \w cold|strong="G5593"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w about|strong="G3195"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w vomit|strong="G1692"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w mouth|strong="G4750"\w*.\f + \fr 3:16 \ft If the Lord vomits you out, where do you go? Something can only be vomited out if it is in.\f*  
\v 17 \w Because|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w rich|strong="G4145"\w*, \w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w become|strong="G1510"\w* \w wealthy|strong="G4145"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w need|strong="G5532"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w nothing|strong="G3762"\w*,” \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w do|strong="G1492"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w realize|strong="G1492"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w most|strong="G1652"\w* \w wretched|strong="G5005"\w*—yes, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w most|strong="G1652"\w* pitiable \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w poor|strong="G4434"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w blind|strong="G5185"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w naked|strong="G1131"\w*—  
\v 18 \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w counsel|strong="G4823"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* buy \w gold|strong="G5553"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w refined|strong="G4448"\w* \w by|strong="G1537"\w* \w fire|strong="G4442"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w become|strong="G4147"\w* \w rich|strong="G4147"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w white|strong="G3022"\w* \w garments|strong="G2440"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w clothed|strong="G4016"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w nakedness|strong="G1132"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* shamefully exposed; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w anoint|strong="G1472"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w eyes|strong="G3788"\w* \w with|strong="G3844"\w* \w eye|strong="G3788"\w* \w salve|strong="G2854"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* see.  
\v 19 \w As|strong="G3745"\w* \w many|strong="G3745"\w* \w as|strong="G3745"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w love|strong="G5368"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w rebuke|strong="G1651"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w discipline|strong="G3811"\w*;\f + \fr 3:19 \ft Sounds like ‘tough’ love. The Greek word is φιλεω, not αγαπαω. See Hebrews 12:6.\f* \w so|strong="G3767"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* zealous \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w repent|strong="G3340"\w*!   
\p
\v 20 “ ‘\w Now|strong="G2532"\w* \w then|strong="G2532"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w stand|strong="G2476"\w* \w at|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w door|strong="G2374"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w knock|strong="G2925"\w*.\f + \fr 3:20 \ft Although this text is widely used in evangelism, it is actually directed to Christians. The Lord is offering fellowship and communion to those who claim to belong to Him. Recall that the Father \+nd seeks\+nd* those who will worship Him in spirit and truth (John 4:23). Many have the impression that God is hard to find or reach, but He disagrees: “You will seek me and find me, when you search for me with all your heart” (Jeremiah 29:13). The trouble is that few of us are willing to meet the condition. See also 2 Chronicles 15:2 and 16:9; also Acts 17:27.\f* \w If|strong="G1437"\w* \w anyone|strong="G5100"\w* \w should|strong="G5100"\w* \w hear|strong="G5456"\w* \w my|strong="G3708"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w*\f + \fr 3:20 \ft Evidently He both knocks and calls. In many cultures one calls out rather than knocks [there may not be any door, or the dogs may not let you get near it], and in the Apurinã culture (an indigenous people in the Amazon jungle, among whom I lived for several years) you call the person's name.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* open \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w door|strong="G2374"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* really \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w come|strong="G1525"\w* \w in|strong="G1909"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w eat|strong="G1172"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.  
\v 21 \w To|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w overcomes|strong="G3528"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w grant|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w sit|strong="G2523"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w*, \w just|strong="G5613"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w overcame|strong="G3528"\w*\f + \fr 3:21 \ft “Consider Him who endured such hostility from sinners against Himself…” (Hebrews 12:3; see also verses 4-11). He overcame, we must overcome—God is not offering a free ride.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w sat|strong="G2523"\w* \w down|strong="G2523"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w*.’\f + \fr 3:21 \ft Comparing this statement with Ephesians 1:19-21 and 2:6, what is the picture? Since the Son is now literally “seated” at the Father's right hand, this promise should be taken literally. But how about right now? I take it that we are supposed to be conducting ourselves on the basis of our position in Christ, on the basis of His victory and authority—maybe this has something to do with ‘overcoming’.\f*   
\p
\v 22 “\w He|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G5101"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w an|strong="G2192"\w* \w ear|strong="G3775"\w* \w let|strong="G2192"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w hear|strong="G5101"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w churches|strong="G1577"\w*.”   
\c 4  
\ms1 “The things that must happen after these”  
\m
\v 1 \w After|strong="G3326"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w looked|strong="G3708"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \nd wow\nd*—\w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w door|strong="G2374"\w* standing open \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sky|strong="G3772"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w first|strong="G4413"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* heard, \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w trumpet|strong="G4536"\w* \w speaking|strong="G2980"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*,\f + \fr 4:1 \ft This is a reference to 1:10 above, so it is the glorified Christ who is speaking—He is continuing His communicating (see 1:1 above), only now He is speaking from Heaven.\f* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Come|strong="G1096"\w* \w up|strong="G1210"\w* \w here|strong="G5602"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w show|strong="G1166"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w must|strong="G1163"\w* \w take|strong="G1096"\w* \w place|strong="G1096"\w* \w after|strong="G3326"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w*.”\f + \fr 4:1 \ft “After these” opens and closes the verse. ‘These’ is a pronoun, so what is its antecedent? Presumably the churches described in chapters 2 and 3 (“the things that are” referred to in 1:19). Does “after” the churches imply that they are off the scene?\f*   
\s1 The Throne Room  
\p
\v 2 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w immediately|strong="G2112"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1096"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w*,\f + \fr 4:2 \ft Compare 1:10. The Voice commanded him to “come up here”—it was something John had to do; I take it that his spirit was transported to heaven. (Consider Jesus—Matthew 17:25, John 1:48; Paul—1 Corinthians 5:3-4, Colossians 2:5; Elisha—2 Kings 5:26, 6:12.)\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w*, \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w* \w set|strong="G2749"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w heaven|strong="G3772"\w* (\w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w One|strong="G3588"\w* \w sitting|strong="G2521"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w*)  
\v 3 \w similar|strong="G3664"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w appearance|strong="G3706"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w stone|strong="G3037"\w*,\f + \fr 4:3 \ft The throne, not the One. 15% of the Greek manuscripts do have the One looking like a stone, but I judge that the 85% are correct.\f* \w jasper|strong="G2393"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w carnelian|strong="G4556"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \it there was\it* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w rainbow|strong="G2463"\w* \w around|strong="G2943"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w*, \w similar|strong="G3664"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w appearance|strong="G3706"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w an|strong="G2532"\w* \w emerald|strong="G4664"\w*.  
\v 4 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w around|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w twenty-four|strong="G1501"\w* \w thrones|strong="G2362"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w thrones|strong="G2362"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* saw \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w twenty-four|strong="G1501"\w* \w elders|strong="G4245"\w* \w sitting|strong="G2521"\w*,\f + \fr 4:4 \ft Why do we have “the” twenty-four elders the first time they are mentioned? I take it that John found them to be especially impressive or interesting (perhaps he identified with them).\f* \w clothed|strong="G4016"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w white|strong="G3022"\w* \w robes|strong="G2440"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w golden|strong="G5552"\w* \w crowns|strong="G4735"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w heads|strong="G2776"\w*.\f + \fr 4:4 \ft Might this picture have any connection with the promise in 3:21 above?\f*  
\v 5 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w* \w came|strong="G2532"\w* lightnings \w and|strong="G2532"\w* noises \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w thunders|strong="G1027"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w lamps|strong="G2985"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w fire|strong="G4442"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w burning|strong="G2545"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w*, \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w spirits|strong="G4151"\w*\f + \fr 4:5 \ft There is no definite article with “seven spirits”. I doubt that they represent the Holy Spirit.\f* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*;  
\v 6 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w sea|strong="G2281"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w glass|strong="G5193"\w*, \w similar|strong="G3664"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w crystal|strong="G2930"\w*.  
