\p
\v 5 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w elders|strong="G4245"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*: “\w Stop|strong="G3361"\w* \w weeping|strong="G2799"\w*! \w Look|strong="G2400"\w*! \w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lion|strong="G3023"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w tribe|strong="G5443"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w Judah|strong="G2455"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Root|strong="G4491"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w David|strong="G1138"\w*, \w has|strong="G3708"\w* \w prevailed|strong="G3528"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* open \w the|strong="G2532"\w* scroll \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w its|strong="G1537"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w seals|strong="G4973"\w*.”  
\v 6 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w midst|strong="G3319"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w four|strong="G5064"\w* \w living|strong="G2226"\w* beings, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w midst|strong="G3319"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w elders|strong="G4245"\w*, \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \nd Lamb\nd* \w standing|strong="G2476"\w*\f + \fr 5:6 \ft The Lamb is a Lion; the Lion is a Lamb. I would say that the Lamb characterizes Christ in His first advent to this earth, while the Lion characterizes His second advent.\f*—\w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w if|strong="G5613"\w* slaughtered, \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w horns|strong="G2768"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w eyes|strong="G3788"\w*, \w which|strong="G3739"\w*\f + \fr 5:6 \ft In about ¾ of the Greek manuscripts, including the best group, the gender of this relative pronoun agrees with “horns” (neuter) and not “eyes” (masculine). Perhaps the spirits were represented by both the horns and the eyes, possibly referring to power and knowledge.\f* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w spirits|strong="G4151"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w sent|strong="G2316"\w* \w out|strong="G2532"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*.  
\v 7 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G2064"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w took|strong="G2983"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w right|strong="G1188"\w* \w hand|strong="G1188"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w One|strong="G3588"\w* \w sitting|strong="G2521"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w*!   
\s2 A new song  
\p
\v 8 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w took|strong="G2983"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* scroll \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w four|strong="G5064"\w* \w living|strong="G2226"\w* beings \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w twenty-four|strong="G1501"\w* \w elders|strong="G4245"\w* \w fell|strong="G4098"\w* \w down|strong="G4098"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* Lamb, \w each|strong="G1538"\w* \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w harps|strong="G2788"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w golden|strong="G5552"\w* \w bowls|strong="G5357"\w* \w full|strong="G1073"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* incenses, \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w prayers|strong="G4335"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* saints.\f + \fr 5:8 \ft They all fell down, but I gather that it was the elders who had harps and bowls and sang the \+nd new\+nd* song (the four are saying “Holy, holy” all the time).\f*  
\v 9 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* sing \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w new|strong="G2537"\w* \w song|strong="G5603"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*:  
\q1 “\w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* worthy \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w take|strong="G2983"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* scroll  
\q2 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* open \w its|strong="G3956"\w* \w seals|strong="G4973"\w*;  
\q1 \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* slaughtered,  
\q2 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* redeemed \nd \+w us|strong="G3004"\+w*\nd*\f + \fr 5:9 \ft Every Greek manuscript except one, of inferior quality, reads “\+nd us\+nd*”. Many modern versions follow that lone manuscript and omit the pronoun, but that leaves the transitive verb “redeem” without a direct object, so they usually supply “men” or some such thing. But the true reading is obviously “us”, so the 24 elders are among the redeemed, and they are already in heaven wearing crowns.\f* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* blood  
\q2 \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w tribe|strong="G5443"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w language|strong="G1100"\w*  
\q2 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w people|strong="G2992"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* ethnic \w nation|strong="G1484"\w*;   
\q1
\v 10 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w You|strong="G1438"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w made|strong="G4160"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*\f + \fr 5:10 \ft A very few late Greek manuscripts read ‘us’, as in KJV, but almost all the manuscripts read “them”. The 24 elders exclude themselves when it comes to reigning on the earth—evidently they will not be involved in the administration of the Messianic Millennial Kingdom.\f* \w kings|strong="G3588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w priests|strong="G2409"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*,  
\q2 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w reign|strong="G2532"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*.”   
\s2 All the angels  
\p
\v 11 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w looked|strong="G3708"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* heard \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w* angels, \w around|strong="G2945"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w living|strong="G2226"\w* beings \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w elders|strong="G4245"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* number \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w ten|strong="G3461"\w* \w thousand|strong="G5505"\w* \w times|strong="G3461"\w* \w ten|strong="G3461"\w* \w thousand|strong="G5505"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w thousand|strong="G5505"\w* \w thousands|strong="G3461"\w*,\f + \fr 5:11 \ft 10,000 x 10,000 = 100,000,000, so the good angels are over 100 million. If we understand correctly from Revelation 12:4 that a third of the original angels followed Lucifer in his rebellion, that means that there are some 50 million demons out there. Good grief!\f*  
\v 12 \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w with|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \nd \+w great|strong="G3173"\+w*\nd* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w*:  
\q1 “Worthy \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lamb|strong="G3004"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* slaughtered  
\q2 \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w receive|strong="G2983"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w power|strong="G1411"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w wealth|strong="G4149"\w*  
\q1 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w wisdom|strong="G4678"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w strength|strong="G2479"\w*  
\q2 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w honor|strong="G5092"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w blessing|strong="G2129"\w*!”\f + \fr 5:12 \ft A list of seven; what else could we add?\f*   
\s2 Every creature  
\p
\v 13 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w creature|strong="G2938"\w* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w heaven|strong="G3772"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w under|strong="G5270"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sea|strong="G2281"\w* (\w the|strong="G1722"\w* existing \it places\it* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w creatures|strong="G2938"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*)—\w I|strong="G3739"\w* heard \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w*\f + \fr 5:13 \ft “Every creature” presumably must include more than men and angels; I take it that all mammals, at least (they have soul), including those in the sea (dolphins, whales), and quite possibly birds (eagles) will participate.\f* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w To|strong="G1519"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w sits|strong="G2521"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Lamb|strong="G3004"\w*: \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w blessing|strong="G2129"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w honor|strong="G5092"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w power|strong="G2904"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w ever|strong="G1519"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w ever|strong="G1519"\w*! Amen!!”  
\v 14 (\w It|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w four|strong="G5064"\w* \w living|strong="G2226"\w* beings \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* “Amen”.) \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w elders|strong="G4245"\w* \w fell|strong="G4098"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* obeisance.\f + \fr 5:14 \ft The living beings and the elders were prostrating themselves and getting up repeatedly.\f*   
\c 6  
\s1 The Lamb opens the seals  
\s2 The \nd first\nd* seal  
\m
\v 1 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lamb|strong="G3004"\w* opened \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w seals|strong="G4973"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* heard \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w four|strong="G5064"\w* \w living|strong="G2226"\w* beings \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w thunder|strong="G1027"\w*, “\w Come|strong="G2064"\w*!”\f + \fr 6:1 \ft The evidence is badly divided here, but I take it that two of the three main independent lines of transmission, including the best one, read as I have translated. The “Come!” was directed to the horse, not to John (since he was right there, there would be no need to address him with a thunderous roar). The same comment applies in verses 5 and 7.\f*  
\v 2 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w looked|strong="G3708"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w*, wow, \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w white|strong="G3022"\w* \w horse|strong="G2462"\w*!\f + \fr 6:2 \ft You had better believe that that was some horse!\f* \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w sat|strong="G2521"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w had|strong="G2192"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w bow|strong="G5115"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w crown|strong="G4735"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w conquering|strong="G3528"\w*, \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w*, \w in|strong="G1909"\w* \w order|strong="G2443"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w conquer|strong="G3528"\w*.   
\s2 The \nd second\nd* seal  
\p
\v 3 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* opened \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w second|strong="G1208"\w* \w seal|strong="G4973"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* heard \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w second|strong="G1208"\w* \w living|strong="G2226"\w* \w being|strong="G2532"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Come|strong="G2064"\w*!”\f + \fr 6:3 \ft Over 80% of the Greek manuscripts do not have “and see”, as in KJV. Each of the living beings called out a horse, saying to it, “Come!”\f*  
\v 4 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w another|strong="G3588"\w* \w horse|strong="G2462"\w* \w went|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w*, fiery \w red|strong="G4450"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w granted|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w sat|strong="G2521"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w take|strong="G2983"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w peace|strong="G1515"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w would|strong="G2532"\w* slaughter each \w other|strong="G3588"\w*; \w also|strong="G2532"\w*, \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w huge|strong="G3173"\w* \w sword|strong="G3162"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*.   
\s2 The \nd third\nd* seal  
\p
\v 5 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* opened \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w third|strong="G5154"\w* \w seal|strong="G4973"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* heard \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w third|strong="G5154"\w* \w living|strong="G2226"\w* \w being|strong="G2532"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Come|strong="G2064"\w*!” \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w looked|strong="G3708"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w*, wow, \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w black|strong="G3189"\w* \w horse|strong="G2462"\w*! \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w sat|strong="G2521"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w had|strong="G2192"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w pair|strong="G2218"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w scales|strong="G2218"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w his|strong="G1909"\w* \w hand|strong="G5495"\w*.  
\v 6 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* heard \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w midst|strong="G3319"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w four|strong="G5064"\w* \w living|strong="G2226"\w* beings \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w A|strong="G5613"\w* ‘\w quart|strong="G5518"\w*’ \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w wheat|strong="G4621"\w* \w for|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w denarius|strong="G1220"\w*\f + \fr 6:6 \ft A denarius was the daily wage for manual labor. To work a full day for a quart of wheat means bare survival.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w three|strong="G5140"\w* ‘\w quarts|strong="G5518"\w*’ \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w barley|strong="G2915"\w* \w for|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w denarius|strong="G1220"\w*; \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w do|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* harm \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w olive|strong="G1637"\w* \w oil|strong="G1637"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w wine|strong="G3631"\w*.”\f + \fr 6:6 \ft Perhaps the oil and wine are spared for their medicinal value.\f*   
\s2 The \nd fourth\nd* seal  
\p
\v 7 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* opened \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w fourth|strong="G5067"\w* \w seal|strong="G4973"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* heard \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w* \w from|strong="G2064"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w fourth|strong="G5067"\w* \w living|strong="G2226"\w* \w being|strong="G2532"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Come|strong="G2064"\w*!”  
\v 8 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w looked|strong="G3708"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w*, wow, \w a|strong="G2532"\w* sickly \w pale|strong="G5515"\w* \w horse|strong="G2462"\w*! \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w as|strong="G1722"\w* \w for|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w sitting|strong="G2521"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w*, \w his|strong="G1909"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w Death|strong="G2288"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* Hades follows \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*.\f + \fr 6:8 \ft The Text does not say that Hades was on a horse. John is stating a fact of human existence: Hades follows death—so it has been for 6,000 years.\f* \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w authority|strong="G1849"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*\f + \fr 6:8 \ft Less than 30% of the Greek manuscripts read ‘them’ for “him”, but they are followed by most (if not all) versions in English. However, it is Death that does the killing; Hades just collects the dead. The 70% are doubtless correct (involving two of the three main independent lines of transmission, including the best one).\f* \w over|strong="G1909"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w fourth|strong="G5067"\w* \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*, \w to|strong="G2532"\w* kill \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w sword|strong="G4501"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w famine|strong="G3042"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w*, \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w wild|strong="G2342"\w* animals \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*.\f + \fr 6:8 \ft ‘The four horsemen of the Apocalypse’ have received quite a bit of press, off and on, but they are just the opening gambit. The really heavy stuff comes later.\f*   
\s2 The \nd fifth\nd* seal  
\p
\v 9 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* opened \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w fifth|strong="G3991"\w* \w seal|strong="G4973"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w underneath|strong="G5270"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w altar|strong="G2379"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w souls|strong="G5590"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w people|strong="G5590"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w had|strong="G2192"\w* \w been|strong="G2192"\w* slaughtered \w on|strong="G3588"\w* \w account|strong="G3056"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Word|strong="G3056"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w on|strong="G3588"\w* \w account|strong="G3056"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w testimony|strong="G3141"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* Lamb \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w held|strong="G2192"\w*.\f + \fr 6:9 \ft These “souls” have evidently not yet been reunited with their bodies, which means that they have not participated in any resurrection, including the Rapture (see 3:10, 4:1 and 5:9). See notes at 7:13-14. “Of the people” excludes animals, that also have souls.\f*  
\v 10 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w cried|strong="G2896"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w with|strong="G1537"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w loud|strong="G3173"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w How|strong="G2193"\w* \w long|strong="G2193"\w*, O Sovereign, Holy \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w True|strong="G3588"\w*, \w until|strong="G2193"\w* \w You|strong="G3004"\w* \w judge|strong="G2919"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w avenge|strong="G1556"\w* \w our|strong="G2532"\w* blood \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w dwell|strong="G2730"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*?”  
\v 11 \w So|strong="G2443"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w white|strong="G3022"\w* \w robe|strong="G4749"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w each|strong="G1538"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* told \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w should|strong="G3195"\w* rest \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w while|strong="G5613"\w* \w longer|strong="G2089"\w*, \w until|strong="G2193"\w* \w both|strong="G2532"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w fellow|strong="G4889"\w* \w slaves|strong="G4889"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* brothers,\f + \fr 6:11 \ft “Slaves” and “brothers” evidently refer to two distinct categories of people, but I don't know the explanation (unless ‘slaves’ refers to Israel, see 7:3 below and Galatians 4:25, in which case ‘brothers’ would refer to the Church).\f* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w about|strong="G5613"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* killed \w just|strong="G5613"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w*, \w should|strong="G3195"\w* \w complete|strong="G4137"\w* \it the number\it*.   
\s2 The \nd sixth\nd* seal  
\p
\v 12 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w*, \w just|strong="G5613"\w* \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* opened \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sixth|strong="G1623"\w* \w seal|strong="G4973"\w*—\w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1096"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w severe|strong="G3173"\w* \w earthquake|strong="G4578"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sun|strong="G2246"\w* \w became|strong="G1096"\w* \w black|strong="G3189"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w sackcloth|strong="G4526"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w hair|strong="G5155"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w moon|strong="G4582"\w* \w became|strong="G1096"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* blood.  
\v 13 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* stars \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w heaven|strong="G3772"\w* \w fell|strong="G4098"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*,\f + \fr 6:13 \ft I suppose this refers to fallen angels, since a single literal star would obliterate our planet.\f* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w fig|strong="G4808"\w* \w tree|strong="G4808"\w* drops \w its|strong="G5259"\w* late \w figs|strong="G3653"\w* \w when|strong="G5613"\w* \w shaken|strong="G4579"\w* \w by|strong="G5259"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w strong|strong="G3173"\w* wind.  
\v 14 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sky|strong="G3772"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* split, \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* scroll \w being|strong="G2532"\w* \w rolled|strong="G1667"\w* \w up|strong="G1667"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w mountain|strong="G3735"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w island|strong="G3520"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w moved|strong="G2795"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w its|strong="G3956"\w* \w place|strong="G5117"\w*.\f + \fr 6:14 \ft Now it starts to get heavy! I have never been in a serious earthquake, but a former colleague was, and the trauma was so severe that years later he still had trouble talking about it.\f*   
\p
\v 15 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w kings|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* magnates \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* generals \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w rich|strong="G4145"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w mighty|strong="G2478"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w slave|strong="G1401"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w free|strong="G1658"\w* \w man|strong="G4145"\w*, \w hid|strong="G2928"\w* \w themselves|strong="G1438"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w caves|strong="G4693"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w among|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w rocks|strong="G4073"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w mountains|strong="G3735"\w*.\f + \fr 6:15 \ft The wrath of God is a great leveler; the social classes all of a sudden do not make much difference—they are all trying to hide.\f*  
