\v 7 \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w tribe|strong="G5443"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w Simeon|strong="G4826"\w* \w twelve|strong="G1427"\w* \w thousand|strong="G5505"\w*,  
\q2 \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w tribe|strong="G5443"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w Levi|strong="G3017"\w* \w twelve|strong="G1427"\w* \w thousand|strong="G5505"\w*,  
\q2 \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w tribe|strong="G5443"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w Issachar|strong="G2466"\w* \w twelve|strong="G1427"\w* \w thousand|strong="G5505"\w*,   
\q1
\v 8 \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w tribe|strong="G5443"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w Zebulun|strong="G2194"\w* \w twelve|strong="G1427"\w* \w thousand|strong="G5505"\w*,  
\q2 \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w tribe|strong="G5443"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w Joseph|strong="G2501"\w*\f + \fr 7:8 \ft “Joseph” stands for Ephraim. Since Levi is counted here (usually he isn't) and Joseph has two tribes, Manasseh and Ephraim, someone has to be dropped—Dan. From both Jacob (Genesis 49:16-17) and Moses (Deuteronomy 33:22) he got the least impressive ‘blessing’.\f* \w twelve|strong="G1427"\w* \w thousand|strong="G5505"\w*,  
\q2 \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w tribe|strong="G5443"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* Benjamin \w twelve|strong="G1427"\w* \w thousand|strong="G5505"\w* were \w sealed|strong="G4972"\w*.\f + \fr 7:8 \ft Linguistically speaking, in terms of the norms of language, a phrase like “the tribe of Asher” can only have one meaning, precisely the meaning that it has everywhere else in the Bible. Ezekiel chapter 37 makes very clear that ‘the ten lost tribes’ are not lost at all—God knows exactly who and where they are, and at the right moment they will be restored.\f*   
\s2 A multitude from the Great Tribulation  
\p
\v 9 \w After|strong="G3326"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3956"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w looked|strong="G3708"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* wow, \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w great|strong="G4183"\w* \w multitude|strong="G3793"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w no|strong="G3762"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w could|strong="G1410"\w* \w number|strong="G3793"\w*, \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* ethnic \w nations|strong="G1484"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w tribes|strong="G5443"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w peoples|strong="G2992"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w languages|strong="G1100"\w*, \w standing|strong="G2476"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Throne|strong="G2362"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* Lamb, \w clothed|strong="G4016"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w white|strong="G3022"\w* \w robes|strong="G4749"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \it having\it* \w palm|strong="G5404"\w* \w branches|strong="G5404"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w hands|strong="G5495"\w*.  
\v 10 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w shouted|strong="G2896"\w* \w with|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w loud|strong="G3173"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Saved|strong="G4991"\w* \w by|strong="G1909"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w sits|strong="G2521"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w by|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lamb|strong="G3004"\w*!”   
\p
