\p
\v 13 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w elders|strong="G4245"\w* reacted, \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, “\w Who|strong="G5101"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w clothed|strong="G4016"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w white|strong="G3022"\w* \w robes|strong="G4749"\w*,\f + \fr 7:13 \ft I take it that we should refer back to the fifth seal, 6:11 above—in that event those martyrs were also killed during the Great Tribulation, just earlier on. Perhaps at this point (7:13) the predetermined number of martyrs is now complete (in 6:11 it was not).\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w where|strong="G4159"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w*?”  
\v 14 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w My|strong="G1722"\w* \w lord|strong="G2962"\w*, \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w*.”\f + \fr 7:14 \ft John understands that the elder is offering information and tells him to go ahead.\f* \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*: “\w These|strong="G3778"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Great|strong="G3173"\w* \w Tribulation|strong="G2347"\w*—\w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w washed|strong="G4150"\w* \w their|strong="G1438"\w* \w robes|strong="G4749"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w made|strong="G3021"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w white|strong="G3021"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* blood \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Lamb|strong="G3004"\w*.\f + \fr 7:14 \ft Assuming a pre-Abomination-of-Desolation rapture of the Church (because of the surprise factor, but see the note at 2 Thessalonians 2:2), I take it that multiplied millions of church members will be left behind—they knew the Gospel but were never really regenerated. When they see that they have been left behind they will fall on their faces before God saying: “Oh Lord, have mercy; if I never believed before I do now!” There will be many millions of conversions in the first hours after the Rapture. People were saved in the OT without the indwelling Holy Spirit, and they will be too. But they will have to face the Beast and most of them will be martyred. Notice that they say, “Saved by our God… and by the Lamb.” Apparently there is a sovereign act of God (the Father) involved here, with the blood of the Lamb as the basis.\f*  
\v 15 \w Therefore|strong="G1223"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w* \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w serve|strong="G3000"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w day|strong="G2250"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w night|strong="G3571"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w His|strong="G1438"\w* \w sanctuary|strong="G3485"\w*.\f + \fr 7:15 \ft How does one “serve” in this sanctuary? I suppose by worship and praise.\f* \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w sits|strong="G2521"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* shelter \w them|strong="G3588"\w*.  
