\v 17 \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* Lamb \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w midst|strong="G3319"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w* shepherds \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w leads|strong="G3594"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w springs|strong="G4077"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w waters|strong="G5204"\w*\f + \fr 7:17 \ft That is what the Text says, “waters”, plural. Might there be different kinds of water, or just different sources?\f* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w life|strong="G2222"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w wipe|strong="G1813"\w* \w away|strong="G1813"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w tear|strong="G1144"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w their|strong="G1438"\w* \w eyes|strong="G3788"\w*.”\f + \fr 7:17 \ft To do this, will He also remove the memories that bring the tears?\f*   
\c 8  
\s1 The \nd seventh\nd* seal  
\m
\v 1 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w when|strong="G3752"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* opened \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w seventh|strong="G1442"\w* \w seal|strong="G4973"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1096"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* stillness \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w heaven|strong="G3772"\w* \w for|strong="G1722"\w* \w about|strong="G5613"\w* \w half|strong="G2256"\w* \w an|strong="G2532"\w* \w hour|strong="G2256"\w*.\f + \fr 8:1 \ft A ‘deafening’ silence! I wonder why. Well, there has been a lot of noise up to this point, and there will be plenty more later, so the silence acts as an emphasis by contrast. The outpouring of wrath will now build to a crescendo.\f*  
\v 2 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* angels \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w stood|strong="G2476"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w trumpets|strong="G4536"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*.\f + \fr 8:2 \ft One gains the clear impression that the seven trumpets form the content of the seventh seal.\f*   
\p
