\c 11  
\s2 The two witnesses  
\m
\v 1 \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w reed|strong="G2563"\w* \w like|strong="G3664"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w measuring|strong="G2563"\w* \w rod|strong="G4464"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* angel \w stood|strong="G3588"\w*\f + \fr 11:1 \ft I get the impression that the angel shifted position, probably with both feet on land—his legs had been spread or straddled, now he stands normally.\f* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w Rise|strong="G1453"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w measure|strong="G3354"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w temple|strong="G3485"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w altar|strong="G2379"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w worship|strong="G4352"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w*.  
