\v 3 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w*\f + \fr 11:3 \ft Presumably the angel is still speaking—might He be God the Son? Could a mere angel say “\+nd my\+nd* two witnesses”?\f* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* \it authority\it* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G1325"\w* \w two|strong="G1417"\w* \w witnesses|strong="G3144"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w prophesy|strong="G4395"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w thousand|strong="G5507"\w* \w two|strong="G1417"\w* \w hundred|strong="G1250"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w sixty|strong="G1835"\w* \w days|strong="G2250"\w*, \w clothed|strong="G4016"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w sackcloth|strong="G4526"\w*.”\f + \fr 11:3 \ft Note that their ‘ministry’ covers 3½ years; the Text does not actually say that it will be simultaneous with the trampling of the holy city, but I imagine that it will come close. When I see the perversity in the world I am sometimes tempted to wish I could do what they are going to do, until I get to the ‘sackcloth’—walking around in sackcloth for 3½ years does not sound like much fun.\f*   
\p
