\p \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w dragon|strong="G1404"\w* \w stood|strong="G2476"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w woman|strong="G1135"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w about|strong="G3195"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w give|strong="G5088"\w* \w birth|strong="G5088"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w order|strong="G2443"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w devour|strong="G2719"\w* \w her|strong="G1438"\w* \w Child|strong="G5043"\w* \w as|strong="G1519"\w* \w soon|strong="G3752"\w* \w as|strong="G1519"\w* \w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w gave|strong="G5088"\w* \w birth|strong="G5088"\w*.  
\v 5 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w she|strong="G2532"\w* bore \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w Son|strong="G5207"\w*, \w a|strong="G2532"\w* male,\f + \fr 12:5 \ft That is what the Text says. Since “Son” is obviously masculine, adding “a male” emphasizes the gender. What the first man lost the second Man (1 Corinthians 15:47) recovered; the first man allowed his wife to lead, the second Man will rule with a rod of iron.\f* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w would|strong="G3195"\w* \w shepherd|strong="G4165"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w nations|strong="G1484"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w rod|strong="G4464"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w iron|strong="G4603"\w*.\f + \fr 12:5 \ft Here the Child is clearly identified as the Messiah—since He was born some 2,000 years ago we are obviously looking at an historical parenthesis. The rebellion of Lucifer and his angels goes back at least 6,000 years. We do not normally associate ‘shepherd’ with ‘a rod of iron’—the Messianic Millennial Kingdom will be a benevolent dictatorship.\f* \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w her|strong="G3956"\w* \w Child|strong="G5043"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* snatched \w up|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w His|strong="G3956"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w*.   
\p
