\s2 A beast from the sea  
\m
\v 1 \w Now|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w*\f + \fr 13:1 \ft Less than 10% of the Greek manuscripts have ‘he’ (presumably referring to the dragon). The difference is between ΕϹΤΑΘΗΝ (I stood) and ΕϹΤΑΘΗ (he stood)—it would be easy to drop off the final Ν, especially since it is similar to Η (more so in handwriting).\f* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* standing \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w seashore|strong="G2281"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* prey \w coming|strong="G2342"\w* \w up|strong="G2532"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sea|strong="G2281"\w*,\f + \fr 13:1 \ft I am not sure that this beast is the same as the one in 11:7—they are said to come from different places (but see 17:8).\f* \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w heads|strong="G2776"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w ten|strong="G1176"\w* \w horns|strong="G2768"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w his|strong="G1909"\w* \w horns|strong="G2768"\w* \w ten|strong="G1176"\w* \w diadems|strong="G1238"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w his|strong="G1909"\w* \w heads|strong="G2776"\w* blasphemous \w names|strong="G3686"\w*.\f + \fr 13:1 \ft There is a family resemblance—seven heads, ten horns; might the Beast be the son of the Dragon? (Imitating God is Satan's ‘thing’.)\f*  
\v 2 \w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w beast|strong="G2342"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w similar|strong="G3664"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w leopard|strong="G3917"\w*, \w his|strong="G2532"\w* \w feet|strong="G4228"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w bear|strong="G2532"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w his|strong="G2532"\w* \w mouth|strong="G4750"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w lion|strong="G3023"\w*'s \w mouth|strong="G4750"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w dragon|strong="G1404"\w* \w gave|strong="G1325"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w his|strong="G2532"\w* \w power|strong="G1411"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w his|strong="G2532"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w great|strong="G3173"\w* \w authority|strong="G1849"\w*.  
\v 3 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w his|strong="G1519"\w* \w heads|strong="G2776"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w if|strong="G5613"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w had|strong="G2532"\w* \w been|strong="G2532"\w* mortally \w wounded|strong="G4969"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w his|strong="G1519"\w* \w fatal|strong="G2288"\w* \w wound|strong="G4127"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w healed|strong="G2323"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w whole|strong="G3650"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w* \w marveled|strong="G2296"\w* \w after|strong="G3694"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w*.   
\p
\v 4 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* obeisance \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w dragon|strong="G1404"\w* \w who|strong="G5101"\w* \w had|strong="G2532"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w authority|strong="G1849"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* obeisance \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Who|strong="G5101"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w like|strong="G3664"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G5101"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w able|strong="G1410"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w make|strong="G2532"\w* \w war|strong="G4170"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*?”  
\v 5 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G2532"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w mouth|strong="G4750"\w* \w speaking|strong="G2980"\w* \w great|strong="G3173"\w* \w things|strong="G3173"\w*, \w that|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G2532"\w*, blasphemy; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G2532"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w authority|strong="G1849"\w*\f + \fr 13:5 \ft I take it that here and in verse 7 it is God who does the giving—this is part of the Plan.\f* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w make|strong="G4160"\w* war forty-two \w months|strong="G3376"\w*.  
\v 6 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* opened \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w mouth|strong="G4750"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w his|strong="G1519"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* blasphemy \w against|strong="G4314"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* blaspheme \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w tabernacle|strong="G4633"\w*, \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w dwell|strong="G4637"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Heaven|strong="G3772"\w*.\f + \fr 13:6 \ft Compare 1 Corinthians 3:16. We are the ‘temple’ of God; those who dwell in Heaven are His tabernacle.\f*  
\v 7 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w make|strong="G4160"\w* \w war|strong="G4171"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* saints \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w conquer|strong="G3528"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w authority|strong="G1849"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w over|strong="G1909"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w tribe|strong="G5443"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w language|strong="G1100"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* ethnic \w nation|strong="G1484"\w*.  
\v 8 \w All|strong="G3956"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w dwell|strong="G2730"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w do|strong="G2532"\w* obeisance \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*, \w whose|strong="G3739"\w* \w names|strong="G3686"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w been|strong="G2532"\w* \w written|strong="G1125"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Book|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Life|strong="G2222"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* Lamb slaughtered \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w foundation|strong="G2602"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*.\f + \fr 13:8 \ft 1 Peter 1:20 makes clear that it was actually before the foundation of the world. God knew what was going to happen before He created the human race, the terrible price He would have to pay, but He went ahead anyway.\f*   
\p
\v 9 \w If|strong="G1487"\w* \w anyone|strong="G5100"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w an|strong="G2192"\w* \w ear|strong="G3775"\w*, \w let|strong="G2192"\w* him hear.  
\v 10 \w If|strong="G1487"\w* \w anyone|strong="G5100"\w* \w has|strong="G4102"\w* captivity, \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w goes|strong="G5217"\w* \w away|strong="G5217"\w*.\f + \fr 13:10 \ft Two of the three main independent lines of transmission (including the best one) so read. The third line reads, ‘If anyone goes away into captivity…’—the second half of the conditional clause (the apodosis) is missing. The rendering of KJV and NKJV reflects a very few late manuscripts. But what does the Text mean? Anyone who has been appointed to captivity will certainly be taken away.\f* \w If|strong="G1487"\w* \w anyone|strong="G5100"\w* kills \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sword|strong="G3162"\w*, \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sword|strong="G3162"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w must|strong="G1163"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* killed. \w Here|strong="G5602"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w endurance|strong="G5281"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* saints.\f + \fr 13:10 \ft I confess that this sentence puzzles me. Well, if I believe that my God is Sovereign over all, that He knows what He is doing, and that He has my ultimate well-being in view (Romans 8:28), then I will endure in faith.\f*   
\s2 A beast from the land  
\p
\v 11 \w Now|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w another|strong="G3588"\w* \w beast|strong="G2342"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* prey \w coming|strong="G2342"\w* \w up|strong="G2532"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w land|strong="G1093"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w had|strong="G2192"\w* \w two|strong="G1417"\w* \w horns|strong="G2768"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* lamb \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w spoke|strong="G2980"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w dragon|strong="G1404"\w*.  
