\v 14 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w deceives|strong="G4105"\w* \w my|strong="G1325"\w* own \it people\it*,\f + \fr 13:14 \ft “My own \+it people\+it*”—two of the three main independent lines of transmission (including the best one) so read. Since John is speaking (writing), his physical people would be the Jews, while his spiritual people would be the Christians. The use of “own” points toward the physical, which accords with the information given elsewhere (Daniel 9:27) that Israel makes a deal with the Beast.\f* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w dwelling|strong="G2730"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*, \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w signs|strong="G4592"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w perform|strong="G4160"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w*, \w telling|strong="G3004"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w dwell|strong="G2730"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w make|strong="G4160"\w* \w an|strong="G2192"\w* \w image|strong="G1504"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w had|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sword|strong="G3162"\w* \w wound|strong="G4127"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w lived|strong="G2730"\w*.  
\v 15 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w granted|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* \w breath|strong="G4151"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w image|strong="G1504"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w image|strong="G1504"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w* \w should|strong="G3588"\w* \w actually|strong="G2532"\w* \w speak|strong="G2980"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w should|strong="G3588"\w* \w cause|strong="G4160"\w* \w as|strong="G3745"\w* \w many|strong="G3745"\w* \w as|strong="G3745"\w* \w would|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w worship|strong="G4352"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w image|strong="G1504"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* killed.\f + \fr 13:15 \ft Worship an image or be killed—how humiliating! It sounds like a rerun of Daniel 3.\f*  
\v 16 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w causes|strong="G4160"\w* \w everyone|strong="G3956"\w*—\w both|strong="G2532"\w* \w small|strong="G3398"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w great|strong="G3173"\w*, \w both|strong="G2532"\w* \w rich|strong="G4145"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w poor|strong="G4434"\w*, \w both|strong="G2532"\w* \w free|strong="G1658"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w slave|strong="G1401"\w*—\w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w receive|strong="G1325"\w* marks \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w right|strong="G1188"\w* \w hand|strong="G5495"\w* \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w foreheads|strong="G3359"\w*,  
\v 17 \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w no|strong="G3361"\w* \w one|strong="G5100"\w* \w would|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w able|strong="G1410"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* buy \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w sell|strong="G4453"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w does|strong="G2192"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w mark|strong="G5480"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w* \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* number \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w his|strong="G2192"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w*.  
\v 18 \w Here|strong="G5602"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w wisdom|strong="G4678"\w*: \w let|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w understanding|strong="G3563"\w* evaluate \w the|strong="G2532"\w* number \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w*, \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* number \w of|strong="G2532"\w* man—\w his|strong="G2532"\w* number \w is|strong="G1510"\w* 666.\f + \fr 13:18 \ft I find this verse difficult to translate. The main verb has two basic meanings: ‘to calculate’ and ‘to vote’. Since the number is immediately provided, what is there to calculate? In the context, any wise person will vote against the number, that is, refuse to receive it, but the idea of ‘against’ is not stated. The number itself is represented by three letters (in Greek), the middle one looking rather like a snake. (Some versions write out the number, but since it has to fit on forehead or hand, just the three letters seems more likely.) Note that the number is 600 plus 60 plus 6, not 6 plus 6 plus 6.\f*   
\c 14  
\s2 The Lamb and the 144,000  
\m
\v 1 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* wow, \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* Lamb \w standing|strong="G2476"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w Mount|strong="G3735"\w* \w Zion|strong="G4622"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w hundred|strong="G1540"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w forty-four|strong="G5062"\w* \w thousand|strong="G5505"\w*,\f + \fr 14:1 \ft Is this group different than the one in chapter 7?\f* \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w His|strong="G1909"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w*\f + \fr 14:1 \ft Only 2% of the Greek manuscripts do not have “His name and” (as in KJV and NKJV), so they had two names written, the Father's and the Son's—much better than having the name of the Beast!\f* \w His|strong="G1909"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*'\w s|strong="G2192"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w written|strong="G1125"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w foreheads|strong="G3359"\w*.  
\v 2 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* heard \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w sound|strong="G5456"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sky|strong="G3772"\w*, \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sound|strong="G5456"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w* \w waters|strong="G5204"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sound|strong="G5456"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w loud|strong="G3173"\w* \w thunder|strong="G1027"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sound|strong="G5456"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* heard \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w harpists|strong="G2790"\w* \w playing|strong="G2789"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w harps|strong="G2788"\w*.\f + \fr 14:2 \ft Evidently John is finding it difficult to describe exactly what he heard, doubtless different from the normal sounds of this earth.\f*  
\v 3 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* sing \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w new|strong="G2537"\w* \w song|strong="G5603"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Throne|strong="G2362"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w four|strong="G5064"\w* \w living|strong="G2226"\w* beings \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w elders|strong="G4245"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w no|strong="G3762"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w able|strong="G1410"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w learn|strong="G3129"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w song|strong="G5603"\w* \w except|strong="G1487"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* 144 \w thousand|strong="G5505"\w*, \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w had|strong="G2532"\w* \w been|strong="G2532"\w* redeemed \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*.  
\v 4 \w These|strong="G3778"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* ones \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w defiled|strong="G3435"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w women|strong="G1135"\w*, \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w virgins|strong="G3933"\w*;\f + \fr 14:4 \ft All the pronouns are masculine, so these are male virgins.\f* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* ones \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w follow|strong="G3326"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* Lamb \w wherever|strong="G3699"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w go|strong="G5217"\w*. \w These|strong="G3778"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* redeemed \w by|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G1510"\w*\f + \fr 14:4 \ft Two of the three main lines of independent transmission (including the best one) read “by Jesus”.\f* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w among|strong="G3326"\w* \w men|strong="G3778"\w*, firstfruits \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* Lamb;\f + \fr 14:4 \ft Why “firstfruits”? Before the advent of refrigeration, food could be preserved by drying, smoking, salting, etc., but by the time of the next harvest, nothing would compare with a firstfruit, which would be something special. Those men were special!\f*  
\v 5 \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w lie|strong="G5579"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w found|strong="G2147"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w mouth|strong="G4750"\w*, \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* blameless.\f + \fr 14:5 \ft These are remarkable men! KJV and NKJV add “before the throne of God”, following the TR which is here based on only two very late manuscripts.\f*   
\s2 Three angels  
\p
\v 6 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w another|strong="G3588"\w* angel \w flying|strong="G4072"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w midheaven|strong="G3321"\w*, \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w an|strong="G2192"\w* eternal \w gospel|strong="G2098"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w proclaimed|strong="G2097"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* reside \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*—\w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* ethnic \w nation|strong="G1484"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w tribe|strong="G5443"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w language|strong="G1100"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w people|strong="G2992"\w*—  
\v 7 \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w loud|strong="G3173"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w*, “\w Fear|strong="G5399"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w*,\f + \fr 14:7 \ft Of all the people who have ever lived on this earth, what percentage of them ever heard that Jesus died for them? Romans 1:18-21 gives the essence of God's requirement: the evidence of creation demands a Creator, and He expects people to acknowledge Him and try to please Him.\f* \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w hour|strong="G5610"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* judging \w has|strong="G2316"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w* obeisance \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w made|strong="G4160"\w* \w heaven|strong="G3772"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*, \w the|strong="G1722"\w* ocean \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w springs|strong="G4077"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w water|strong="G5204"\w*.”\f + \fr 14:7 \ft As fresh, pure water becomes more and more scarce, the springs of water will become increasingly important.\f*   
\p
\v 8 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w another|strong="G3739"\w*, \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w second|strong="G1208"\w*, angel followed, \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w It|strong="G2532"\w* \w fell|strong="G4098"\w*, \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w fell|strong="G4098"\w*, Babylon \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w great|strong="G3173"\w*!—\w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w made|strong="G4222"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w nations|strong="G1484"\w* \w drink|strong="G4222"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w wine|strong="G3631"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w rage|strong="G2372"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w her|strong="G3956"\w* \w fornication|strong="G4202"\w*.”\f + \fr 14:8 \ft Why “rage”? Her fornication was violent and compulsive, also insatiable.\f*   
\p
\v 9 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w another|strong="G5100"\w* angel, \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w third|strong="G5154"\w*, followed \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w loud|strong="G3173"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w*: “\w If|strong="G1487"\w* \w anyone|strong="G5100"\w* \w worships|strong="G4352"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w his|strong="G1722"\w* \w image|strong="G1504"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w receives|strong="G2983"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w mark|strong="G5480"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w his|strong="G1722"\w* \w forehead|strong="G3359"\w* \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w his|strong="G1722"\w* \w hand|strong="G5495"\w*,\f + \fr 14:9 \ft To actually serve as a warning, this would have to be contemporary with 13:16.\f*  
\v 10 really, \nd \+w he|strong="G2532"\+w*\nd* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w drink|strong="G4095"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w wine|strong="G3631"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* fury \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w mixed|strong="G2767"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w full|strong="G1722"\w* strength \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w cup|strong="G4221"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w wrath|strong="G3709"\w*. \w In|strong="G1722"\w* fact, \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* tormented \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w fire|strong="G4442"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w sulfur|strong="G2303"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* holy angels \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* Lamb.”  
\v 11 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w smoke|strong="G2586"\w* \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* torment goes \w up|strong="G1519"\w* \w forever|strong="G1519"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w ever|strong="G3756"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w rest|strong="G2192"\w* \w day|strong="G2250"\w* \w or|strong="G2532"\w* \w night|strong="G3571"\w*, \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w worship|strong="G4352"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w his|strong="G1519"\w* \w image|strong="G1504"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w whoever|strong="G3588"\w* \w receives|strong="G2983"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w mark|strong="G5480"\w* \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w his|strong="G1519"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w*.\f + \fr 14:11 \ft Believe me, you do not want to submit to the Beast in any way! Don't let anyone put anything on your right hand or on your forehead. Better to be executed. I do not doubt that the Beast is already alive on the earth, with age and preparation sufficient to take center stage at any moment.\f*   
\p
\v 12 \w Here|strong="G5602"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w endurance|strong="G5281"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* saints, \w here|strong="G5602"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w keep|strong="G5083"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w commands|strong="G1785"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*.\f + \fr 14:12 \ft I would say that the two “here”s are cataphoric, referring forward to the content of verse 13.\f*  
\v 13 \w I|strong="G2532"\w* heard \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w heaven|strong="G3772"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w me|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Write|strong="G1125"\w*: ‘\w Blessed|strong="G3107"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w dead|strong="G3498"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* die \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w now|strong="G2532"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w*’ (“\w Yes|strong="G3483"\w*” \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*), ‘\w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* rest \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w labors|strong="G2873"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w follow|strong="G3326"\w* \w along|strong="G2532"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*.’ ”   
\s2 The earth is harvested  
\p
\v 14 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* wow, \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w white|strong="G3022"\w* \w cloud|strong="G3507"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* someone \w like|strong="G3664"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w son|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w man|strong="G5207"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w sitting|strong="G2521"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w cloud|strong="G3507"\w*, \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w his|strong="G1722"\w* \w head|strong="G2776"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w golden|strong="G5552"\w* \w crown|strong="G4735"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w his|strong="G1722"\w* \w hand|strong="G5495"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w sharp|strong="G3691"\w* \w sickle|strong="G1407"\w*.  
\v 15 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w another|strong="G3588"\w* angel \w came|strong="G2064"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w temple|strong="G3485"\w* \w crying|strong="G2896"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w loud|strong="G3173"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w sitting|strong="G2521"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w cloud|strong="G3507"\w*, “Thrust \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w sickle|strong="G1407"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w reap|strong="G2325"\w*, \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w time|strong="G5610"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w reap|strong="G2325"\w* \w has|strong="G5610"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w harvest|strong="G2326"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* dry.”  
\v 16 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w sitting|strong="G2521"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w cloud|strong="G3507"\w* swung \w his|strong="G1909"\w* \w sickle|strong="G1407"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* harvested.   
\p
\v 17 \w Then|strong="G2532"\w* \w another|strong="G3588"\w* angel \w came|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w temple|strong="G3485"\w* (\w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w heaven|strong="G3772"\w*), \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w too|strong="G2532"\w* \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w sharp|strong="G3691"\w* \w sickle|strong="G1407"\w*.  
\v 18 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w another|strong="G3588"\w* angel \w came|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w altar|strong="G2379"\w* (\w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w authority|strong="G1849"\w* \w over|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w fire|strong="G4442"\w*), \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w called|strong="G3004"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w with|strong="G1537"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w loud|strong="G3173"\w* \w cry|strong="G5456"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sharp|strong="G3691"\w* \w sickle|strong="G1407"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, “Thrust \w in|strong="G1909"\w* \w your|strong="G2192"\w* \w sharp|strong="G3691"\w* \w sickle|strong="G1407"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w gather|strong="G5166"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* grape \w clusters|strong="G1009"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w vine|strong="G1093"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w her|strong="G3754"\w* \w grapes|strong="G4718"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* ripe.”  
\v 19 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* angel swung \w his|strong="G1519"\w* \w sickle|strong="G1407"\w* \w at|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w gathered|strong="G5166"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w vine|strong="G1093"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* threw \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w winepress|strong="G3025"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s \w terrible|strong="G3173"\w* fury.  
\v 20 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w winepress|strong="G3025"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w trampled|strong="G3961"\w* \w outside|strong="G1855"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w city|strong="G4172"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* blood \w came|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w winepress|strong="G3025"\w* \w up|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w horses|strong="G2462"\w*' \w bridles|strong="G5469"\w*, \w for|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w thousand|strong="G5507"\w* \w six|strong="G1812"\w* \w hundred|strong="G1812"\w* stadia.\f + \fr 14:20 \ft That is roughly 180 miles! If some four billion people will be killed during the seven-year period [mostly the second half of it] (as I calculate, a low estimate) and we allow an average of one gallon of blood per person, that is four billion gallons of blood—which would make quite a river! If the “winepress of God's terrible fury” described here represents sort of a summary of the blood shed during the Great Tribulation period, then the picture is not far fetched. Of course a winepress has a single outlet and the liquid is conveyed to the receptacle by a conduit of appropriate size. In this case the conduit is 180 miles long and the flow is about four feet (1.33 yards) deep—four billion gallons equals about 20 million cubic yards; 180 miles equals about 320 thousand linear yards; so we have about 62.5 cubic yards of blood per linear yard of conduit—so the conduit is about 45 yards wide. My purpose in conducting this exercise is simply to show that the description of the “winepress of God's terrible fury” is not at all ridiculous—it is a graphic but factual picture of the coming bloodbath.\f*   
\c 15  
\s1 Here come the bowls!  
\m
\v 1 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w another|strong="G3588"\w* \w sign|strong="G4592"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w heaven|strong="G3772"\w*, \w great|strong="G3173"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w marvelous|strong="G2298"\w*: \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* angels \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w seven|strong="G2033"\w* \w last|strong="G2078"\w* \w plagues|strong="G4127"\w*—\w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* fury \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w completed|strong="G5055"\w*.\f + \fr 15:1 \ft I take it that this is a generic cover statement, referring to the detailed description that follows. I further take it that these ‘bowl’ plagues relate to the seventh trumpet (11:15) and make up the third ‘woe’ (11:14).\f*   
\s2 The song of the victors  
\p
\v 2 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w sea|strong="G2281"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w glass|strong="G5193"\w* \w mingled|strong="G3396"\w* \w with|strong="G1537"\w* \w fire|strong="G4442"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w prevailed|strong="G3528"\w* \w over|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Beast|strong="G2342"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w over|strong="G1909"\w* \w his|strong="G1909"\w* \w image|strong="G1504"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w over|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* number \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w his|strong="G1909"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w*, \w standing|strong="G2476"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* glassy \w sea|strong="G2281"\w*, \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w harps|strong="G2788"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.\f + \fr 15:2 \ft These people were martyred by order of the Beast, so how did they ‘prevail’ over him? By refusing to bow to him they escaped from hell (14:11); they died physically but won spiritually (but see 12:11).\f*  
\v 3 \w They|strong="G2532"\w* sing \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w song|strong="G5603"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w Moses|strong="G3475"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w slave|strong="G1401"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w song|strong="G5603"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lamb|strong="G3004"\w*, \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*:  
\q1 “\w Great|strong="G3173"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w marvelous|strong="G2298"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w Your|strong="G2962"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w*,  
\q2 O \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Almighty|strong="G3841"\w*!  
